description:
.NET Commons Library is originally inspired by the Apache Commons project stack for java applications. It is intended to be .NET equivalent of Apache Commons and it is built to provide the common software components and basic application stack for developing .NET applications. It includes the following components: Commons.Utils provides the basic utilities for .NET applications. Commons.Collections provides the extended collection implementation based on System.Collections.Generics. Commons.Json provides a JSON parser and composer to dynamically manipulate json object with the power of "dynamic" keyword in .net. 
        Please report issues to https://github.com/yanggujun/commonsfornet/issues
summary: The .NET Commons Library provides extended generic collections, data structures, utilities and a dynamic JSON parser and composer. The Commons Library includes following data structures, collections and utitlies: MurmurHash3, MurmurHash, FNVHash, Closure, Factory, Equator, Transformer, murmur, hash, fnv, functions, functors, basic, TreeMap, SortedMap, NavigableMap, BidirectionalMap, LruMap, HashedMap, ReadOnlyMap, HashMap, LinkedHashedMap, MultiValueMap, MultiMap, MultiValueHashedMap, MultiValueTreeMap, ReferenceMap, LinkedMap, LinkedHashMap, OrderedMap, SkipList, SkipListMap, SkipListSet, TreeBimap, PriorityQueue, CompositeCollection, TreeBag, HashedBag, HashBag, BoundedQueue, Deque, MaxPriorityQueue, MinPriorityQueue, HashedSet, TreeSet, LinkedDeque, LinkedSet, ReferenceSet, LruSet, ReadOnlyBimap, hash, least, recently, used, map, dictionary, cache, tree, sorted, ordered, navigable, multivalue, multi, value, bidirectional, bimap, priority, queue, deque, linked, hashed, reference, skip, list, composite, collection, collections, bag, max, min, fibonacci heap, left leaning red black tree and a JSON parser and composer which can dynamically manipulate the JSON string and object without create dedicated strong typed classes.
